    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 57</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 19</em>, <em>Advanced Player's Guide pg. 183</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> 1 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> 2 lbs.<br/><strong>Category</strong> Adventuring Gear</p><h2 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/>Description</h2><p>Sounding a horn requires a DC 10 Perform (wind instruments) check and can convey concepts such as 'Attack!', 'Help!', 'Advance!', 'Retreat!', 'Fire!', and 'Alarm!' The report of a signal horn can be clearly heard (Perception DC 0) up to a half-mile distant. For each quarter-mile beyond, Perception checks to hear the horn take a -1 penalty.</p>",
